---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LightEstimator from "../components/LightEstimator.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Houseplant Window Light Estimator"
  description="Estimate houseplant light from window direction, distance from glass, and obstruction before choosing a plant location."
  canonicalPath="/light-meter/"
>
  <section class="content">
    <p class="eyebrow">Flagship tool</p>
    <h1>Houseplant Window Light Estimator</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This tool gives a conservative starting estimate for apartment plant placement. It is not a replacement for a real light meter,
      but it is useful when you need to decide where to put a plant today.
    </p>
  </section>
  <LightEstimator />
  <section class="content">
    <h2>How to validate the estimate</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Check for leaning or longer gaps between leaves after two to four weeks.</li>
      <li>Move sun-sensitive leaves back if they bleach, crisp, or develop pale patches.</li>
      <li>Prefer a phone lux app or dedicated meter when placing expensive or flowering plants.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Evidence label:</strong> This is a practical decision aid based on common indoor-light patterns, not laboratory measurement.
      Future experiment updates should replace assumptions with measured lux readings from repeatable room setups.
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
